request.description:
Fetch all skill categories with their skills.

Use this query to test caching performance:
- First call: DB query (slower)
- Subsequent calls: Cached response (faster)

Expected response:
```json
{
  "data": {
    "skillCategories": [
      {
        "category": "Backend",
        "skills": ["Java", "Python", "Spring", ...]
      },
      ...
    ]
  }
}
```

body.raw:
{
  "query": "query SearchMatches($mode: UserMode!, $skills: [String!]!, $experience: String!) { searchMatches(mode: $mode, skills: $skills, experience: $experience) { matches { id title company score skills experience } vectorVisualization { skill isCore x y } } }",
  "variables": {
    "mode": "CANDIDATE",
    "skills": ["Java", "Spring", "React"],
    "experience": "3-5 Years"
  }
}

